            <title>[PIG-1642] Order by doesn&apos;t use estimation to determine the parallelism</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1642</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1249&quot; title=&quot;Safe-guards against misconfigured Pig scripts without PARALLEL keyword&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1249&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1249&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, a simple heuristic is used to determine the number of reducers if it isn&apos;t specified (via PARALLEL or default_parallel). For order by statement, however, it still defaults to 1.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
